ge` to connect to socket in `initState` and listen for `match:created`\n4. Disco
nnect in `dispose`\n\nWait, adding userId to AuthState would change auth bloc wh
ich is beyond the scope of matching. But it\'s necessary for socket connection. 
Alternatively, I can get it from `AuthRepository.getMe()` in HomePage initState.
\n\nActually, a cleaner approach: in `HomePage.initState`, after requesting reco
mmendations, also call `_initSocket()`. In `_initSocket()`, I can get the userId
from an API call or from a shared source. But this is inefficient.\n\nBetter app
roach: modify `AuthBloc` to store `userId` in `AuthAuthenticated` state. This is
a minimal change and is directly needed for the socket feature.\n\nWait, looking
at the review report again, it says:\n> 1. 在 `apps/mobile/lib/core/network/` 或
