ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now let me fix the Controller direct Gateway dependency (Issue 6). I 
need to move the emit logic to the Service, and have the Controller just call Se
rvice.\n\nLooking at the current controller:\n```typescript\nif (result.isMatch 
&& result.matchId) {\n  const summaryForActor = await this.matchingService.getMa
tchSummary(\n    result.matchId,\n    user.userId,\n  );\n  const summaryForTarg
et = await this.matchingService.getMatchSummary(\n    result.matchId,\n    dto.t
arget_id,\n  );\n\n  if (summaryForActor && summaryForTarget) {\n    this.matchi
ngGateway.emitMatchCreated(\n      user.userId,\n      dto.target_id,\n      sum
maryForActor,\n      summaryForTarget,\n    );\n  }\n}\n```\n\nI need to move th
is to the Service. But the Service doesn\'t have access to the Gateway. I can in
ject the Gateway into the Service, but the review says:\n> 模块之间通过 **Interf
ace / EventEmitter** 解耦，禁止直接 import 其他模块的内部 Service\n\nActually, t
he Gateway is in the same module (matching). So injecting MatchingGateway into M
atchingService should be fine - they\'re in the same module. The issue is Contro
ller directly calling Gateway.\n\nLet me re-read the review:\n> Controller 直接
注入 `MatchingGateway` 并调用 `emitMatchCreated`。根据 `nestjs.md` 分层原则，模
块之间应通过 **Interface / EventEmitter** 解耦，禁止直接 import 其他模块的内部 S
ervice/Gateway。Gateway 属于实时通信层，不应被 Controller 直接依赖。\n\nThe fix 
is to move the emit logic to Service. Since Gateway is in the same module, Servi
ce can depend on it. Alternatively, use EventEmitter.\n\nActually, looking at th
e module:\n```typescript\nproviders: [MatchingService, MatchingGateway],\nexport
s: [MatchingService, MatchingGateway],\n```\n\nThe simplest fix is to inject Mat
chingGateway into MatchingService and have Service handle the emit. But actually
, a cleaner approach per the review is:\n> 方案 A：在 `MatchingService.recordSwi
peAction` 返回结果中包含 "是否需要发送通知" 的标记，由 Controller 调用 Service 
后，将通知逻辑委托给 `EventEmitter` 或独立 NotificationService。\n> 方案 B：将 `
emitMatchCreated` 调用下沉到 `MatchingService` 中，Controller 只负责调用 Service
。\n\nOption B is simpler. Let me move the gateway emission to the service. I\'l
l inject `MatchingGateway` into `MatchingService` and add a method `notifyMatchC
reated` or just do it inside `recordSwipeAction`.\n\nActually, looking at the cu
rrent `recordSwipeAction`, it returns `{ isMatch, matchId, conversationId }`. I 
could modify it to also handle the notification. But the notification needs `get
MatchSummary` which needs the matchId. \n\nLet me think about this carefully. Th
e current flow:\n1. Controller calls `recordSwipeAction`\n2. Controller checks `
isMatch`\n3. Controller calls `getMatchSummary` twice\n4. Controller calls `matc
hingGateway.emitMatchCreated`\n\nIf I move step 2-4 into `recordSwipeAction`, th
e service becomes responsible for notification. This is option B.\n\nLet me impl
ement this:\n1. Remove `MatchingGateway` from `MatchingController` constructor\n
2. Remove the emit logic from `MatchingController.recordAction`\n3. Inject `Matc
hingGateway` into `MatchingService` constructor\n4. Add the notification logic i
nside `MatchingService.recordSwipeAction` or as a separate method\n\nActually, `
recordSwipeAction` currently returns `{ isMatch, matchId, conversationId }`. If 
I add notification there, it would need the actorId and targetId, which it alrea
dy has. Let me do it inside `recordSwipeAction`.\n\nWait, but `recordSwipeAction
` doesn\'t currently need the Gateway. Adding it there makes the service respons
ible for real-time communication. That\'s acceptable since they\'re in the same 
module.\n\nLet me implement Option B: move the emit logic to `MatchingService`.'
,
